  "prompt": "I have given class 10 exam in 2014 ,and I am giving 12 exam in 2017 .am I eligible for JEE 2017 as I will appear for 1st time?",
  "response": "To be eligible for the Joint Entrance Examination (JEE) in 2017, candidates generally must have completed their Class 12 exam or its equivalent in the year of the exam or in the previous year. \n\nBased on the information you've provided, you completed your Class 10 exam in 2014 and are appearing for your Class 12 exam in 2017. If you are giving your Class 12 exam for the first time in 2017, you should be eligible to apply for JEE 2017, provided you meet the other eligibility criteria set by the examination authorities (such as minimum percentage marks in Class 12, subjects studied, etc.).\n\nMake sure to check the specific eligibility criteria mentioned on the official JEE website or the information bulletin for JEE 2017, as different years may have slight variations in eligibility requirements.",
